<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PaLTM3.3.10">
<l>puṟṟara valku lacōtainal lāycci taṉ puttiraṉ kōvin taṉai</l>
<l>kaṟṟiṉam mēyttu varakkaṇ ṭukantavaḷ kaṟpitta māṟṟa mellām</l>
<l>ceṟṟami lātavar vāḻtaru teṉputu vaiviṭ ṭucit taṉcol</l>
<l>kaṟṟivai pāṭaval lārkaṭal vaṇṇaṉ kaḻaliṇai kāṇpār kaḷē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who are able to sing these calf[-songs] composed by Viṭṭucittaṉ of Putuvai in the South, </l>
<l rend="indent">where those without enmity live happily,</l>
<l>[on] all the words of command of the good herdess Yaśodā,</l>
<l rend="indent">with hips [like] a serpent in an ant-hill,</l>
<l>[spoken] when, seeing her son Govinda return,</l>
<l rend="indent">having grazed the calf herd, she rejoiced,</l>
<l>They will see the Sea-hued Lord’s pair of feet.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
